
## Environment Setup
Create a .env file in the project root with the following entry:
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your_api_key

Install required modules:
pip install -r requirements.txt


## Crawl
The crawler can be configured by adjusting the `crawl-config.yaml` file.
To run a crawl:

docker run --rm \
  -v "$PWD/crawl-config.yaml:/app/crawl-config.yaml" \
  -v "$PWD/crawls:/crawls" \
  webrecorder/browsertrix-crawler crawl \
  --config /app/crawl-config.yaml


## Generate Annotations
Run the following commands depending on the model:

GPT-5
make run-results

TinyLlama
make run-tl

Note: the tinyllama model will need downloading in .gguf format, and placed inside models. 
https://huggingface.co/TheBloke/TinyLlama-1.1B-Chat-v1.0-GGUF